# Quality and Completion

A task is complete only when requirements, scope, assumptions, exclusions, and acceptance criteria are explicit; changes are limited to approved scope; validation evidence or checks not run are listed; independent code-quality review follows implementation; engineering-risk review occurs when triggered; documentation, migration, compatibility, and versioning implications are addressed; unresolved risks are explicit; and release readiness stops before publication, deployment, signing, submission, or release.
